    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">*EDIT* Okay, after further review, take out the cart and start the Pony, or put in Sam and bid 3-4 starting the Green Dragon Inn. Either way, this deck rocks. Thanks for all the helpful reviews!<br />
<BR><br />
<BR><br />
<br />
Like I said in the intro, this deck is all about the shadow. As a lark, I tried to give this deck a theme, and came up with the NWO. You gotta admit, the picture of Saruman on "Saruman&#39;s Ambition" looks like Hollywood Hogan (Whatcha gonna do?). Anyways, Using Ambition to make your uruk&#39;s cheap, and snows and spies to hamper your opponent&#39;s archery and skirmishes, the damage +1 text just plain kills most companions. Use the Savagery&#39;s wisely, especially when you can gain an easy kill. By site 9, there shouldn&#39;t be too much left, and with your minions being even cheaper at the slopes, you should have an easy kill.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
As for the fellowship, it is a simple ranger/archer deck with Elrond to draw up what you need. Using the Cart to drop whatever you don&#39;t need can be a real help, plus starting with the lookout point can really hamper some people&#39;s strategy (getting out Aragorn with the Pony, or Sam with the Dragon Inn). I used the King because Arwen is in the deck. On the average, I like Ranger of the North better, except when Arwen is a starting companion. I do not see her as expendable when I start her. <br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
I do not think I have to explain the Adventure Path, except for the first and last sites. Other than that, it is pretty self explanatory. <br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
Well, if you have read this far, I hope you like what you saw. I think this deck is solid and fun to play, and remember, "nWo is just... 2... SWEEEET!"  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
